<title type="html"><![CDATA[Horizontal lists]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=61&amp;p=309#p309"><![CDATA[
Making horizontal lists out of ULs, LIs etc is currently a hack.<br /><br />You have to change from a list-item display type to an inline display type. Because of this &quot;hack&quot;, you cannot have horizontal lists with bullets (images or other style bullets). Or rather, you can have a bullet but that's another hack (background-image, content injection).<br /><br />So, can I propose a horizontal-list-item display type?<br /><br />I obviously have not thought out the full consequences of this - for example, how would you handle nested lists with horizontal-list-item? Do you use a vertical indent for nest lists? <br /><br />I'm just a simple web dev who is struggling to produce simple and elegant HTML+CSS without hacks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=107">rbirkby</a> — Tue May 29, 2007 7:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
